r%20with%20dynamite%20and%20plotted%20to%20ram%20the%20vehicle%20into%20Kennedy's%20limo%20in%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20Florida%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fthe-kennedy-assassin-who-failed-153519612%2F%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20He%20was%20motivated%20by%20his%20intense%20hatred%20of%20Catholics%20and%20the%20Kennedy%20family%2C%20but%20backed%20off%20when%20he%20saw%20that%20the%20president%20was%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20young%20children.%20Pavlick%20was%20later%20arrested%20and%20institutionalized%20until%201966%2C%20three%20years%20after%20Kennedy%20was%20assassinated%20by%20Lee%20Harvey%20Oswald%20while%20visiting%20Dallas%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%2013%20other%20presidents%20all%20experienced%20serious%20assassination%20threats%20and%20ultimately%20survived%20%E2%80%94%20and%20these%20are%20only%20the%20most%20dramatic%2C%20most-publicized%20instances.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20has%20thwarted%20many%20more%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%2013%20presidents%20who%20escaped%20attempts%20on%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAndrew%20Jackson%20survived%20an%20assassination%20attempt%20in%201835%20when%20the%20shooter's%20gun%20misfired.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222695%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sketch%20of%20Andrew%20Jackson%20being%20confronted%20by%20a%20gunman%20outside%20the%20Capitol%20in%201835.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6693461b9caa6ed01e016ff1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221996%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20sketch%20of%20Andrew%20Jackson%20being%20confronted%20by%20a%20gunman%20outside%20the%20Capitol%20in%201835.%3Cp%3ECORBIS%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20misty%20January%20day%20in%201835%2C%20Richard%20Lawrence%2C%20an%20out-of-work%20house%20painter%20who%20believed%20he%20was%20the%2015th-century%20English%20king%20